The District of Columbia government must fund a new ballpark by December 31 for the Montreal Expos' relocation to Washington.
Baseball commissioner Bud Selig hailed this as a crucial step.
Until the new stadium is ready, games will be held at RFK Stadium.
Major League Baseball expressed displeasure at the legislation requiring private financing for half the construction costs.
Despite initial funding challenges, the Washington Nationals are set to debut in their new city.
The team's future briefly seemed uncertain, but a compromise was reached for public funding.
The Nationals will play their first game against the New York Mets at RFK Stadium before moving to their new home.
